        "header": "4Method",
        "images": [
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.17054/2606.17054v1/figures/method.jpg",
                "caption": "Figure 3:HUGarchitecture.Conditioned on an RGB-D image and a query point on the target object,HUGpredicts MANO hand grasps via a flow-matching transformer over fused RGB and point cloud features. Predicted human grasps are then retargeted to robot hands.",
                "position": 457
            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2606.17054/2606.17054v1/figures/bench_grasps.jpg",
                "caption": "Figure 4:Predicted grasps onHUG-Bench.HUG’s predicted grasps for 30 unseen objects across six scenes of theHUG-Benchtestsplit.HUGgeneralizes across a variety of object shapes and sizes, environments, and camera viewpoints. Top row:small_2,medium_1,large_1. Bottom row:large_2,medium_2,small_1. See Appendix TableD.2for the objects in each scene.",
                "position": 467
            }
        ]
    },
